Package com.hexaforce.warzone.controllers

Class MapController

java.lang.Object
com.hexaforce.warzone.controllers.MapController
public class MapController extends Object
The MapController class is responsible for managing map-related operations in the Warzone game.

    • loadMap

      public Map loadMap(GameContext gameContext, String loadFileName) throws InvalidMap
      Loads a map from a file into the given game context.
      Parameters:
      gameContext - The game context where the map will be loaded.
      loadFileName - The name of the file to load the map from.
      Returns:
      The loaded map.
      Throws:
      InvalidMap - If the loaded map is invalid or cannot be loaded.

    • editMap

      public void editMap(GameContext gameContext, String editFilePath) throws IOException, InvalidMap
      Edits a map based on the contents of an edit file.
      Parameters:
      gameContext - The game context to edit the map within.
      editFilePath - The path to the edit file.
      Throws:
      IOException - If an I/O error occurs during the editing process.
      InvalidMap - If the edited map becomes invalid after the edit.

    • editFunctions

      public void editFunctions(GameContext gameContext, String argument, String operation, Integer switchParameter) throws IOException, InvalidMap, InvalidCommand
      Performs various map editing operations based on the provided arguments, operation, and a switch parameter.
      Parameters:
      gameContext - The game context to perform the operations within.
      argument - The argument for the operation.
      operation - The type of operation to perform.
      switchParameter - An optional switch parameter for the operation.
      Throws:
      IOException - If an I/O error occurs during the editing process.
      InvalidMap - If the edited map becomes invalid after the edit.
      InvalidCommand - If an invalid command is issued during the editing.

    • saveMap

      public boolean saveMap(GameContext gameContext, String fileName) throws InvalidMap
      Saves the current map to a file with the given file name.
      Parameters:
      gameContext - The game context containing the map to be saved.
      fileName - The name of the file to save the map to.
      Returns:
      true if the map was successfully saved, false otherwise.
      Throws:
      InvalidMap - If the map is invalid and cannot be saved.

      gameContext - The game context to reset the map within.
      fileToLoad - The name of the file to load the new map from.
